Persian Gulf Stocks: Al-Mal Investment and Herfy Food Services

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-07-04T12:42:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/persian-gulf-stocks-al-mal-investment-and-herfy-food-services.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 0.2
percent and  Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  added 0.3 percent.
Qatar’s  QE Index (DSM)  was little changed. Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All
Share Index (SASEIDX)  retreated 0.5 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.  Al-Mal Investment Co. (ALMAL KK) gained the most in almost
two months, advancing 2.9 percent to 71 fils. The Kuwaiti
investment company received approval from the central bank to
extend a 10 percent share buyback by six months.        Herfy Food Services Co. (HERFY)   gained as much as 4.9
percent to 91 riyals, the highest level on record, before
closing 0.6 percent higher. The Saudi Arabian fast-food chain
received regulatory approval to raise capital by offering one
new share for every nine held.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
